[In situations such as this, it is appropriate for the laboratory that made
the diagnosis to notify the authorities in the U.S. where the (possibly
viremic) patient had attended the meeting. There may be no cause for
concern if it was not "mosquito season" in that place but that
determination is the responsibility of the local health authorities in the
U.S. - Mod.CHC
